-- Tom Cole Said to Join Citigroup as Co-Head of Leveraged Finance With Matas
-- Kristen Haunss
-- 2010-06-28T22:11:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/tom-cole-said-to-join-citigroup-as-co-head-of-leveraged-finance-with-matas.html

          
          
             Tom Cole , a former co-head of global
banking Americas at  HSBC Holdings Plc , will join  Citigroup Inc. 
as co-head of leveraged finance with  Barbara Matas , according to
a person familiar with the matter.  
 Cole, 49, will join the Americas Capital Markets
Origination Group effective July 19, reporting to  Richard Zogheb 
and  John Chirico , co-heads of the group, said the person, who
declined to be identified because the information was private.
 Alexander Samuelson , a Citigroup spokesman, confirmed the hire.
Cole declined to be interviewed.  
 Citigroup is the fourth-largest underwriter of U.S. high-
yield bonds this year, with 9.9 percent of the $117.5 billion
underwritten, according to data compiled by Bloomberg. Itâ€™s the
sixth-biggest underwriter of leveraged loans, with 5.4 percent
of the $159 billion market year to date, Bloomberg data show.  
 Prior to joining HSBC, Cole worked at  Deutsche Bank AG 
where he was head of leveraged finance, the person said.  
